    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a univariate categorical distribution with five market segments. Synthetic proportions (\u2211=100%) were generated using a Dirichlet distribution (\u03b1=1) to simulate realistic market competition. Values maintain ordinal ranking with FinTech > HealthTech > EdTech > CleanTech > IoT, reflecting typical tech industry distributions. The pie chart format was selected to emphasize part-to-whole relationships, with pattern fills enhancing accessibility for color vision deficiencies. Following Cairo's principles, pattern transformations (rotation/scaling) create unique perceptual signatures for each category while maintaining equal luminance levels. Tufte's data-ink ratio is optimized by using minimal border contrast (#34495e) against a light background. Proportional accuracy is reinforced through dual encoding: angular size (primary) and percentage labels (secondary)."
